- a. the household of origin, specifying: name, surname and date of birth of each member, as well as any absence of one or both parents, in order to identify the correct equivalence scale parameter;
- b. the work activity and the relative gross income received abroad by each household member in the year 2023 (lack of income must be specified in the documentation);


- c. any buildings owned abroad by each household member on 31 December 2023 with the relative area specified as well as the movable assets available abroad on the same date (the absence of real estate assets must be expressly specified in the documentation);
- d. any rental costs incurred for the residence of the household. The payment of any scholarship funds will be suspended until the EQUIVALENT UNIVERSITY ISEE (ISEEUP) is received.


